{
  "_comment": "room-types.json — define what each room key counts toward.",
  "_schema": {
    "_comment": "For each room key, add any category names as properties with integer values.",
    "_values": "Integer = how many of that category this room contributes. 1 is the normal case; use 2 (etc.) for rooms that count double.",
    "_omit": "Leave out a category entirely if the room doesn't belong to it.",
    "_example_closet": {
      "Blueprint": 1,
      "dead-end": 1
    },
    "_example_bunkroom": {
      "BedroomDir": 1,
      "Bedroom": 2,
      "DeadEnd": 2
    }
  },
  "_notes": [
    "Keys here must match the 'key' field in tracker_stats.json (lowercase, spaces/apostrophes stripped, hyphens kept).",
    "Cloister keys in tracker output have hyphens stripped: 'cloister-of-joya' appears as 'cloisterofjoya'.",
    "Spare room upgrades (sparegreenroom, spareroom-master, etc.) share the spare room mesh so they appear as 'spareroom' in the tracker — no way to distinguish them currently.",
    "Variants of a room (bunkroom-gems, bunkroom-gold, bunkroom-keys) are listed separately in case their type counts differ.",
    "The tracker also reads Room.RoomType (a game enum). Values: 0=Generic, 1=Garage, 2=Entrance, 3=Border_buster, 4=Moving, 5=Secret_Garden, 6=Terrace, 7=Clock_tower, 8=Patio, 9=Veranda."
  ],
